hether%20he%20was%20ready%20to%20leave%20his%20post%20if%20it%20meant%20securing%20peace.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20can%20exchange%20this%20for%20NATO%20(membership)%2C%20if%20that%20condition%20is%20there%2C%20immediately%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20president%20added.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cstrong%3EALSO%20READ%3A%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fhas-trump-abandoned-ukraine-in-favour-of-russia-7774931%5C%22%3EOpinion%20%7C%20Has%20Trump%20Abandoned%20Ukraine%20In%20Favour%20Of%20Russia%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EUS%20Changing%20Stance%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20taking%20office%20for%20the%20second%20term%20on%20January%2020%2C%20US%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20has%20pushed%20for%20elections%20to%20take%20place%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20having%20branded%20Zelenskiy%20a%20%26quot%3Bdictator%26quot%3B%2C%20an%20apparent%20reference%20to%20the%20Ukrainian%20leader's%20official%20five-year%20term%20running%20out%20in%202024.%20He%20has%20also%20appeared%20to%20accuse%20Ukraine%20of%20being%20responsible%20for%20the%20war%2C%20which%20Russia%20started%20when%20it%20waged%20a%20full-scale%20invasion%20three%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump's%20criticism%20of%20Zelenskiy%20came%20as%20relations%20between%20the%20two%20leaders%20deteriorated%20sharply%20in%20recent%20weeks.%20Zelenskiy%20has%20opposed%20the%20idea%20of%20elections%20during%20a%20full-scale%20war%2C%20a%20position%20supported%20by%20his%20major%20domestic%20political%20opponents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Ukrainian%20president%20also%20said%20he%20wanted%20to%20see%20Trump%20as%20a%20partner%20to%20Ukraine%20and%20more%20than%20simply%20a%20mediator%20between%20Kyiv%20and%20Moscow.%20%26quot%3BI%20really%20want%20it%20to%20be%20more%20than%20just%20mediation...%20that's%20not%20enough%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20a%20press%20conference%20in%20Kyiv.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cstrong%3EALSO%20READ%3A%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Frussia-holds-the-cards-in-peace-talks-with-ukraine-donald-trump-to-bbc-7753848%5C%22%3ERussia%20Holds%20%26quot%3BThe%20Cards%26quot%3B%20In%20Peace%20Talks%20With%20Ukraine%3A%20Trump%20To%20BBC%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Trump%20wants%20to%20get%20money%20back%20for%20the%20billions%20of%20dollars%20sent%20to%20support%20Ukraine's%20war%20against%20Russia.%20Washington%20is%20negotiating%20with%20Kyiv%20a%20mineral%20resources%20deal%20Trump%20wants%20as%20compensation%20for%20the%20wartime%20aid%20his%20predecessor%20Joe%20Biden%20gave%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20in%20exchange%20Ukraine%20wants%20any%20agreement%20signed%20with%20the%20United%20States%20to%20include%20security%20guarantees%20as%20it%20battles%20Russia's%20nearly%20three-year%20invasion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20Trump%20administration%20has%20initiated%20talks%20with%20Moscow%20to%20discuss%20the%20ending%20of%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20after%20reestablishing%20diplomatic%20relations.%20So%20far%2C%20Kyiv%20has%20been%20kept%20out%20of%20the%20negotiations.%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cstrong%3EALSO%20READ%3A%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fnoone-is-excluding-ukraine-vladimir-putin-tells-zelensky-not-to-be-hysterical-7748817%5C%22%3E%C2%A0%26quot%3BNo%20One%20Is%20Excluding%20Ukraine%26quot%3B%3A%20Putin%20Tells%20Zelensky%20Not%20To%20Be%20%26quot%3BHysterical%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EEconomic%20Strains%20Of%20War%20On%20Russia%20And%20Ukraine%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20clear%20from%20the%20beginning%20that%20Putin's%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20would%20be%20a%20global%20economic%20disaster.%20Inflation%20figures%20released%20on%20either%20side%20of%20the%20border%20showed%20the%20continued%20toll%20the%20conflict%20has%20had%20on%20citizens%20of%20both%20neighbours%20-%20with%20price%20rises%20running%20at%209.5%20per%20cent%20in%20Russia%20and%2012%20per%20cent%20in%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPer%20International%20Monetary%20Fund%20(IMF)%20data%2C%20Russia's%20gross%20domestic%20product%20(GDP)%20slumped%20to%20-1.3%20per%20cent%20at%20the%20outset%20of%20the%20war%20but%20has%20since%20recovered%20to%20post%203.6%20per%20cent%20in%20each%20of%20the%20last%20two%20years.%20But%20now%20the%20Russian%20economy%20is%20showing%20the%20first%20signs%20of%20cooling%2C%20with%20sales%20and%20orders%20falling%20in%20various%20sectors%20due%20to%20high%20interest%20rates%20and%20inflation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAlready%20based%20on%20the%20results%20of%20November%20and%20especially%20December%2C%20we%20see%20that%20growth%20has%20stopped%20being%20frontal...The%20pace%20has%20slowed%20in%20a%20number%20of%20industries%3A%20the%20food%20industry%2C%20the%20chemical%20industry%2C%20wood%20production%2C%20and%20certain%20sectors%20of%20machine%20building...The%20volume%20of%20orders%20from%20businesses%20is%20decreasing%2C%26quot%3B%20Russia's%20Economy%20Minister%20Maxim%20Reshetnikov%20said%20recently.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20his%20ministry%20was%20working%20with%20the%20central%20bank%20and%20finance%20ministry%20to%20link%20monetary%20and%20fiscal%20policy.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20looking%20for%20a%20balance%20between%20curbing%20inflation%20and%20economic%20growth%2C%26quot%3B%20Reshetnikov%20was%20cited%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20far%2C%20despite%20wide-ranging%20US%20and%20European%20sanctions%2C%20Russian%20factories%20have%20continued%20to%20source%20the%20components%20and%20raw%20materials%20needed%20to%20keep%20the%20war%20machine%20going%2C%20according%20to%20a%20report%20by%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22No%20Follow%2C%20No%20Index%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2025%2Ffeb%2F22%2Fwhat-have-three-years-of-putins-war-done-to-both-nations-economies%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Guardian%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPer%20the%20report%2C%20the%20influx%20of%20funds%20from%20the%20illicit%20sale%20of%20oil%2C%20and%20to%20a%20lesser%20extent%20natural%20gas%2C%20nickel%20and%20platinum%2C%20has%20allowed%20for%20an%20expansion%20of%20a%20state%20apparatus%20that%2018%20months%20ago%20looked%20on%20its%20knees.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Ukraine%20is%20holding%20better%20as%20an%20independent%20nation%20as%20its%20GDP%2C%20which%20sunk%2036%20per%20cent%20by%20the%20summer%20of%202022%2C%20rebounded%20to%205.3%20per%20cent%20in%202023%20and%203%20per%20cent%20in%202024.%20But%2C%20according%20to%20Ukraine's%20economy%20ministry%20forecast%2C%20GDP%20growth%20is%20expected%20to%20slow%20to%202.7%20per%20cent%20this%20year%2C%20below%20the%203-4%20per%20cent%20expected%20by%20most%20Ukrainian%20analysts%20and%20economists.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUkraine%20is%20holding%20strong%20on%20its%20electricity%20market%20and%20metal%20deposits.%20Per%20The%20Guardian%20report%2C%20imports%20of%20electricity%20have%20jumped%20by%20a%20half%20from%20123GWh%20to%20183GWh%20from%20January%202024%20to%20last%20month%2C%20and%20exports%20have%20soared%20from%20just%205GWh%20to%2085GWh%20over%20the%20same%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELooking%20to%20the%20next%2010%20years%2C%20Ukraine%20has%20a%20wealth%20of%20metal%20deposits%2C%20many%20of%20them%20rare%2C%20that%20some%20estimates%20put%20at%20%2411tn.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3ELosses%20On%20Ground%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThousands%20of%20Ukrainian%20citizens%20have%20died%20and%20over%206%20million%20live%20as%20refugees%20abroad%20since%20Russian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20ordered%20the%20invasion%20by%20land%2C%20sea%20and%20air.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMilitary%20losses%20have%20been%20catastrophic%2C%20although%20they%20remain%20closely%20guarded%20secrets.%20Public%20Western%20estimates%20based%20on%20intelligence%20reports%20vary%20widely%2C%20but%20most%20say%20hundreds%20of%20th