egularly%20at%20pick-up.%20For%20some%20millennials%2C%20grandparents%20are%20an%20important%20part%20of%20our%20family%20ecosystem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bb58ab5c-d5ce-432b-a72b-4513a4b7925c%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20heavily%20considered%20their%20proximity%20to%20us%20when%20choosing%20a%20home%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20choosing%20our%20first%20home%2C%20it%20was%20important%20to%20us%20to%20have%20easy%20access%20to%20my%20mom%20and%20my%20in-laws%2C%20who%20are%20less%20than%2030%20minutes%20away%2C%20to%20ensure%20that%20our%20children%20could%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flessons-learned-living-with-my-jewish-grandparents-2021-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esee%20their%20grandparents%20frequently%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Both%20sets%20of%20parents%20are%20in%20their%20mid%20to%20late%2070s%3B%20I%20had%20my%20first%20child%20at%2036%20and%20my%20second%20at%2040%2C%20so%20their%20time%20together%20is%20precious.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20my%20youngest%20first%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchildcare-too-expensive-unaffordable-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eattended%20day%20care%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20she%20only%20went%20three%20days%20a%20week.%20My%20mom%20and%20in-laws%20surprised%20me%20by%20offering%20to%20watch%20her%20the%20other%20two%20days%20so%20I%20could%20work%20full-time%20without%20paying%20for%20full-time%20care.%20I'm%20sure%20they%20would%20have%20offered%20even%20if%20they%20lived%20further%20away%2C%20having%20them%20relatively%20close%20has%20made%20a%20huge%20difference.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a9091790-b37c-427b-9ebf-771235d115dc%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhile%20they%20might%20not%20understand%20our%20new%20parenting%20systems%2C%20they%20try%20hard%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20grateful%20that%20neither%20my%20in-laws%20nor%20my%20mom%20have%20ever%20questioned%20modern%20millennial%20parenting%20values%20and%20concepts.%20I'm%20sure%20they%20are%20internally%20rolling%20their%20eyes%20at%20me%20when%20I%20talk%20about%20sleep%20hygiene%2C%20bottle%20schedules%2C%20and%20gentle%20parenting.%20But%20they%20genuinely%20try%20to%20stick%20to%20my%20schedules%20and%20notes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20found%20that%20my%20part%20of%20this%20relationship%20is%20letting%20things%20go%20that%20aren't%20make-or-break%3B%20my%20child%20will%20be%20OK%20if%20someone%20forgets%20to%20put%20them%20in%20a%20sleep%20sack%20for%20a%20nap%20or%20if%20my%20mom%20makes%20a%20bottle%20by%20hand%20instead%20of%20using%20our%20fancy%20formula%20machine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThankfully%2C%20none%20of%20them%20has%20ever%20given%20me%20long%20diatribes%20about%20how%20they%20did%20things%20when%20we%20were%20babies.%20This%20mutual%20respect%20is%20what%20keeps%20our%20relationship%20healthy%2C%20and%20I'm%20grateful%20that%20they're%20open%20to%20learning%20the%20ways%20we%20think%20are%20best%20for%20our%20children%20at%20this%20point%20in%20time%2C%20no%20matter%20how%20ridiculous%20they%20might%20seem%20to%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c4a016a7-44ae-4f01-bf7d-de18fd82af2f%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI've%20learned%20to%20pick%20my%20battles%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20first-time%20mom%20suffering%20from%20postpartum%20anxiety%2C%20I%20would%20internally%20flip%20out%2C%20watching%20them%20feed%20my%20toddler%20things%20riddled%20with%20added%20sugar%20and%20salt.%20It's%20been%20four%20years%20since%20I%20had%20my%20first%20child%20and%20their%20first%20grandchild.%20I've%20now%20realized%20their%20time%20together%20is%20more%20important%20than%20the%20details.%20While%20I%20would%20prefer%20that%20my%20preschooler%20not%20get%20diet%20tea%20sweetened%20with%20stevia%2C%20her%20tea%20party%20is%20much%20more%20important%20than%20what's%20in%20her%20cup.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225ee10218-19ff-4ea6-ad4d-91bd3c13344a%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThey%20are%20there%20when%20we%20need%20them%20most%3C%2Fs