s%20recently%20as%20January.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGhost%20actors%2C%20located%20in%20China%2C%20conduct%20these%20widespread%20attacks%20for%20financial%20gain%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20says.%20%26quot%3BAffected%20victims%20include%20critical%20infrastructure%2C%20schools%20and%20universities%2C%20healthcare%2C%20government%20networks%2C%20religious%20institutions%2C%20technology%20and%20manufacturing%20companies%2C%20and%20numerous%20small-%20and%20medium-sized%20businesses.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fransomware-attacks-corporations-children-executives-mandiant-google-cyber-security-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERansomware%20is%20a%20type%20of%20malware%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20lets%20bad%20actors%20encrypt%20a%20victim's%20data%20until%20they%20pay%20a%20ransom.%20Ransomware%20attacks%20have%20become%20more%20common%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20sometimes%20targeting%20large%20companies%20or%20government%20infrastructure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20ransomware%20attack%20in%20February%202024%20against%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finfamous-hacker-gang-pharmacy-prescription-backlogs-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChain%20Healthcare%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20payment%20arm%20of%20healthcare%20giant%20UnitedHealth%20Group%2C%20briefly%20crippled%20the%20pharmacy%20industry%20after%20it%20caused%20a%20major%20backlog%20in%20filling%20customer%20subscriptions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20ransomware%20hackers%20use%20phishing%20methods%2C%20sending%20fake%20messages%20to%20victims%20in%20the%20hope%20that%20they'll%20click%20a%20link%20and%20install%20malware%20on%20their%20devices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20hackers%20in%20the%20Ghost%20group%2C%20however%2C%20use%20publicly%20available%20code%20to%20exploit%20common%20vulnerabilities%20in%20organizations'%20software%20that%20have%20not%20been%20removed%20by%20updated%20patches%2C%20the%20FBI%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20FBI%20has%20observed%20Ghost%20actors%20obtaining%20initial%20access%20to%20networks%20by%20exploiting%20public-facing%20applications%20that%20are%20associated%20with%20multiple%20Common%20Vulnerabilities%20and%20Exposures%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20warning%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20FBI%20said%20in%20the%20warning%20that%20Ghost%20attackers%20usually%20claim%20that%20they%20will%20sell%20the%20victim's%20stolen%20data%20if%20they%20do%20not%20pay%20a%20ransom.%20However%2C%20the%20agency%20said%20they%20%26quot%3Bdo%20not%20frequently%20exfiltrate%20a%20significant%20amount%20of%20information%20or%20files%2C%20such%20as%20intellectual%20property%20or%20personally%20identifiable%20information%20that%20would%20cause%20significant%20harm%20to%20victims%20if%20leaked.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20FBI%20recommends%20consulting%20its%20StopRansomware%20guide%20for%20comprehensive%20information%20on%20how%20companies%20can%20guard%20against%20ransomware%20attacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20tips%20for%20fighting%20against%20common%20ransomware%20tactics%20are%20to%20maintain%20regular%20system%20backups%20of%20sensitive%20information%2C%20patch%20known%20system%20vulnerabilities%20with%20security%20updates%20and%20use%20phishing-resistant%20multifactor%20authentication%20for%20company%20email%20accounts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20FBI%20recommends%20reporting%20any%20ransomware%20attacks%20to%20the%20agency.%20In%20the%20security%20advisory%2C%20the%20FBI%20said%20it%20is%20particularly%20interested%20in%20%26quot%3Bany%20information%20that%20can%20be%20shared%2C%20including%20logs%20showing%20communication%20to%20and%20from%20foreign%20IP%20addresses%2C%20a%20sample%20ransom%20note%2C%20communications%20with%20threat%20actors%2C%20Bitcoin%20wallet%20information%2C%20and%2For%20decryptor%20files.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fghost-cyberattacks-ransomware-what-you-need-to-know