dividuals.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EOnly%20two%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20top%2050%20philanthropists%20explicitly%20support%20LGBTQIA%2B%20causes.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EOver%20half%20of%20queer%20non-profits%20operate%20with%20annual%20budgets%20below%20Rs%2050%20lakh%2C%20making%20it%20difficult%20for%20them%20to%20scale%20their%20impact.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EInternational%20donors%20contribute%2059%25%20of%20funding%20to%20LGBTQIA%2B%20organisations%20in%20India%2C%20making%20domestic%20funding%20critical%20for%20long-term%20sustainability.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E53%25%20of%20LGBTQIA%2B%20non-profits%20operate%20at%20a%20hyperlocal%20level%2C%20addressing%20specific%20community%20needs%20but%20struggling%20to%20access%20mainstream%20funding.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F02%2FTBI-featured-image-16_11zon-1-1740060364.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22India's%20Queer%20Futures%5Cn%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F02%2FTBI-featured-image-16_11zon-1-1740060364.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F02%2FTBI-featured-image-16_11zon-1-1740060364-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F02%2FTBI-featured-image-16_11zon-1-1740060364-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F02%2FTBI-featured-image-16_11zon-1-1740060364-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F02%2FTBI-featured-image-16_11zon-1-1740060364-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-407731%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EDr%20Aqsa%20Shaikh%2C%20Keshav%20Suri%2C%20Chandini%2C%20Maya%20Sharma%2C%20and%20Radhika%20Piramal%20at%20India%E2%80%99s%20Queer%20Futures%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFor%20years%2C%20Indian%20companies%20have%20spent%20crores%20on%20weddings%20and%20lavish%20celebrations.%20It%E2%80%99s%20time%20they%20invest%20in%20ensuring%20queer%20people%20can%20access%20the%20same%20basic%20rights%20and%20dignities%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Piramal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EFocus%20on%20grassroots%20%26amp%3B%20systemic%20change%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20first%20phase%2C%20the%20Pride%20Fund%20will%20provide%20financial%20support%20to%20eight%20queer-led%20organisations%20chosen%20through%20a%20rigorous%20selection%20process.%20These%20groups%20work%20at%20the%20intersection%20of%20gender%2C%20sexuality%2C%20healthcare%2C%20livelihoods%2C%20and%20social%20justice%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-list%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EBasera%20Samajik%20Sansthan%20(Noida)%20%E2%80%94%20Supporting%20HIV-positive%20individuals%20and%20vulnerable%20groups%2C%20including%20sex%20workers%2C%20MSM%20(men%20who%20have%20sex%20with%20men)%2C%20and%20transgender%20persons.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EDeepshikha%20Samiti%20(Delhi)%20%E2%80%94%20Helping%20people%20with%20HIV%2FAIDS%20find%20employment%20and%20participate%20in%20governance.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EVikalp%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Group%20(Vadodara)%20%E2%80%93%20Working%20for%20the%20rights%20of%20marginalised%20women%20and%20gender%2Fsexual%20minorities%20in%20rural%2C%20tribal%20areas.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ESappho%20for%20Equality%20(Kolkata)%20%E2%80%94%20Fighting%20for%20the%20rights%20and%20social%20justice%20of%20individuals%20with%20non-normative%20gender-sexual%20orientations%20and%20identities.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EKarna%20Subarna%20Welfare%20Society%20(Murshidabad)%20%E2%80%94%20Building%20resilience%20within%20the%20LGBTQIA%2B%20community%20and%20generating%20sustainable%20livelihoods.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EYa_All%3A%20The%20Youth%20Network%20(Manipur)%20%E2%80%94%20A%20queer%2C%20youth-led%20organisation%20working%20on%20mental%20health%2C%20sexual%20health%2C%20and%20economic%20inclusion.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EChhattisgarh%20Mitwa%20Sankalp%20Samiti%20(Chhattisgarh)%20%E2%80%94%20Focused%20on%20the%20development%20and%20mobilisation%20of%20the%20transgender%20community.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EPayana%20(Bengaluru)%20%E2%80%94%20Providing%20advocacy%20services%20and%20support%20to%20local%20sexual%20minority%20communities.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COur%20goal%20is%20not%20just%20to%20give%20grants%20but%20to%20create%20a%20long-term%20funding%20ecosystem%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Parmesh%2C%20who%20identifies%20as%20gay%2C%20and%20has%20long%20advocated%20for%20workplace%20inclusivity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EA%20call%20for%20corporates%20and%20philanthropists%20to%20step%20up%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20fund%E2%80%99s%20organisers%20are%20urging%20businesses%2C%20high-net-worth%20individuals%2C%20and%20corporate%20CSR%20initiatives%20to%20commit%20to%20sustained%20funding%20for%20LGBTQIA%2B%20causes.%20To%20attract%20diverse%20funders%2C%20they%20have%20created%20three%20tiers%20of%20donation%20categories%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-list%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ECatalyst%20(Rs%2025-50%20lakh)%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIlluminator%20(Rs%2050%20lakh%2B)%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EBeacon%20Circle%20(Rs%205%20crore%2B)%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CToday%2C%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20challenges%20is%20that%20the%20critical%20connection%20%E2%80%94%20between%20the%20largest%20corporations%20and%20the%20neediest%20NGOs%20%E2%80%94%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20exist.%20Big%2C%20well-known%20LGBTQIA%2B%20organisations%20do%20get%20funding%20and%20resources%2C%20but%20if%20you%20want%20to%20ensure%20that%20your%20corporate%20money%20is%20reaching%20the%20most%20underfunded%20places%2C%20this%20fund%20is%20a%20bridge%20to%20see%20that%20happen%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Saurabh%20Kirpal%2C%20a%20senior%20advocate%20and%20LGBTQIA%2B%20rights%20crusader%20who%20was%20among%20the%20planners%20behind%20the%20Pride%20Fund.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EA%20new%20chapter%20in%20queer%20philanthropy%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20India%E2%80%99s%20queer%20communities%2C%20the%20Pride%20Fund%20goes%20beyond%20providing%20financial%20support.%20It%20symbolises%20a%20long-awaited%20acknowledgement%20of%20their%20strength%2C%20a%20critical%20step%20toward%20sustainable%20change%2C%20and%20an%20opportunity%20to%20redefine%20the%20landscape%20of%20philanthropy%20with%20a%20focus%20on%20true%20equity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20many%20grassroots%20organisations%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EPride%20Fund%3C%2Fem%3E%20arrived%20at%20a%20crucial%20time%20when%20hope%20was%20fading.%20As%20Sadam%20Hanjabam%2C%20a%20representative%20from%20Ya_All%2C%20shared%20with%20a%20strong%20sense%20of%20emotion%2C%20%E2%80%9COur%20organisation%20was%20about%20to%20shut%20down%20the%20very%20month%20we%20learnt%20about%20the%20fund.%E2%80%9D%20He%20continued%2C%20%E2%80%9CBeing%20an%20organisation%20dedicated%20to%20and%20created%20by%20young%20people%2C%20we%20often%20face%20judgment%20for%20not%20being%20considered%20mature%20enough.%20This%20fund%20will%20be%20a%20lifeline%20for%20our%20sustainability.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F02%2FTBI-featured-image-17_11zon-1740060537.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Aravani%20Art%20Project%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F02%2FTBI-featured-image-17_11zon-1740060537.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F02%2FTBI-featured-image-17_11zon-1740060537-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.c